  "text_preview": "\"none\" ASL American Sign Language ASL University ► American Sign Language: \"none\" NONE: Form \"O\" hands and hold them out in front of you palms facing mostly toward each other and a little bit forward. Then quickly move your hands forward and shake your head \"no\" once. This sign can also be done with one hand. As I'm doing it here, the sign is almost identical to a casual version of TEACH. Here is another example of me signing \"none.\" Note that the hands move forward and a bit toward the outside. Also see: \" NOTHING \" On that page, check out the signs \"hear-nothing\" and \"know-nothing.\" Notes: Question: What is the difference between the sign for TEACH and the sign for NONE? Answer: The sign TEACH is typically done somewhat higher than the sign for NONE. However, the \"casual\" version of the "
